"title": "9511: hell, as a place of punishment",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "9511",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The place of eternal punishment in fire and darkness intended for Satan and his angels, but also for human beings who choose to reject God.</p>\n<h2>Hell was originally created for the devil and his angels</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:41\">MAT 25:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:31\">LUK 8:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:4\">2PE 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:1-Rev20:3\">REV 20:1–20:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:10\">REV 20:10</a></p>\n<h2>Hell is a consequence of rejecting God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:40-Matt13:42\">MAT 13:40–13:42</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:22\">DEU 32:22</a> <em>Fire is often referred to in the OT as a symbol of divine judgment</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:42-Mark9:48\">MRK 9:42–9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:36\">JHN 3:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:8\">ROM 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:9\">1TH 5:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:26-Heb10:29\">HEB 10:26–10:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:7\">2PE 3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:15\">REV 20:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:8\">REV 21:8</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ possesses authority over hell</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:18\">MAT 16:18</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:18\">REV 1:18</a></strong> <em>The Greek word “Hades” often simply means “death”. However, at points it implies the experience of punishment after death.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:27\">JHN 5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:42\">ACT 10:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:31\">ACT 17:31</a></p>\n<h2>The Valley of Hinnom as a figure of hell</h2>\n<h3>The Valley of Hinnom as a geographical feature</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:8\">JOS 15:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:16\">JOS 18:16</a></p>\n<h3>The Valley of Hinnom as a place of child sacrifice</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:3\">2CH 28:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs16:3\">2KI 16:3</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs23:10\">2KI 23:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:6\">2CH 33:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:6\">2KI 21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:35\">JER 32:35</a></p>\n<h3>The Valley of Hinnom as a place of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:30-Jer7:32\">JER 7:30–7:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer19:1-Jer19:15\">JER 19:1–19:15</a></p>\n<h3>The Valley of Hinnom as a synonym for hell</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:28\">MAT 10:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:4-Luke12:5\">LUK 12:4–12:5</a> <em>The word used for “hell” is “Gehenna”, from the Hebrew “Ge Hinnom”, meaning “the Valley of Hinnom”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:29-Matt5:30\">MAT 5:29–5:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:8-Matt18:9\">MAT 18:8–18:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:43-Mark9:48\">MRK 9:43–9:48</a></p>",
